name: 𝐴𝑙𝑦𝑠𝑠𝑢𝑚 𝑚𝑖𝑛𝑢𝑠
description: 𝐴𝑙𝑦𝑠𝑠𝑢𝑚 𝑎𝑙𝑦𝑠𝑠𝑜𝑖𝑑𝑒𝑠 L. is introduced by Carl Linnaeus to Scientific world in 1759. It's Native to Europe and Anatolia. I took that photograph 1200m at Western Taurus Mountains. It is abundant as a weed in waste places nearly throughout that range but you can see it's beauty as a art of nature. Definetly, it should be protected as a part of plant diversity.
